  "response": "The thing that surprised me the most about studying at Oxford was the incredible sense of history and tradition that permeates everything. It's not just the ancient buildings and the portraits of past scholars; it's also the rituals and ceremonies, like wearing formal academic dress for exams, and the sense of being part of a long line of scholars stretching back centuries. It really adds a unique depth and richness to the academic experience.",
